{{Other uses of|Mia Mia|Mia Mia (disambiguation)}}
{{Use Australian English|date=October 2018}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}
A '''mia-mia''' is a temporary [[Shelter (building)|shelter]] made of bark, branches, leaves and grass used by some [[Indigenous Australians]]. The word is also used in [[Australian English]] to mean "a temporary shelter". It comes from the [[Wathaurong|Wada Wurrung]] language. The term is also used in New Zealand, where it is usually spelt ''mai-mai'' and has the slightly different meaning of a [[Waterfowl_hunting#Blinds|shelter or hide used by a duck-hunter]].

