{{Other uses2|Palla}}
[[Image:Livia Drusila - Paestum (M.A.N. Madrid) 01.jpg|right|thumb|200px|Statue of [[Livia Drusilla]], wearing a stola and palla.]]
'''Palla''' is a traditional [[Ancient Rome|ancient Roman]] [[Mantle (clothing)|mantle]] worn by women, fastened by [[brooch]]es.  It was similar to the [[pallium (Roman cloak)|pallium]] that a man would wear. The shape was rectangular instead of semi-circular as with the traditional [[toga]].

